<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     TAB 1: WORKED EXAMPLE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="tab-pane active" id="pane-worked">
<div class="container">

  <div class="scenario">
    <strong>Worked Example:</strong> A <strong>500 kg cow</strong> requires <strong>15% CP</strong> in her diet.
    The ingredients we have to feed her are <strong>Soybean meal</strong> and <strong>Corn</strong>.
    What proportions do we need to mix these two ingredients to obtain a ration that provides her required 15% CP?
  </div>

  <table class="feed-table" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
    <thead><tr><th>Feed ingredient</th><th>CP (% DM)</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Soybean meal</td><td>45%</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Corn</td><td>10%</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div id="w-reveal-container">

    <div class="worked-step" id="w-step1">
      <h4>Step 1 — Identify Box A, B and C</h4>
      <p>One ingredient must have a nutrient value <em>above</em> the target, and one <em>below</em> it. The target (Box A) must sit between the two. It does not matter which ingredient is placed top or bottom on the square — only that one sits above A and one below.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:8px;"><strong>Box A</strong> (centre) = the nutrient requirement = <strong>15% CP</strong></p>
      <p><strong>Box B</strong> = one ingredient = <strong>Soybean Meal, 45% CP</strong> (above target)</p>
      <p><strong>Box C</strong> = other ingredient = <strong>Corn, 10% CP</strong> (below target)</p>
      <p style="margin-top:8px;">✓ Check: is Box A between B and C? &nbsp; 10% &lt; <strong>15%</strong> &lt; 45% — yes, the Pearson Square will work.</p>
    </div>

    <div id="w-step2" style="display:none;">
      <div class="worked-step">
        <h4>Step 2 — Subtract across the diagonal</h4>
        <p>Subtract across the diagonal of the square. Always make any negative results positive — we only care about the <em>difference</em>.</p>
        <div class="ps-outer" style="margin-top:14px;">
          <div class="ps-grid">
            <div class="ps-left">
              <div class="ps-ing"><div class="i-tag">Box B</div><div class="i-name">Soybean Meal</div><div class="i-val">45% CP</div></div>
              <div class="ps-ing"><div class="i-tag">Box C</div><div class="i-name">Corn</div><div class="i-val">10% CP</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="ps-svg-wrap">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 200 200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <rect x="4" y="4" width="192" height="192" fill="none" stroke="#5a8c72" stroke-width="2.5" rx="4"/>
                <line x1="4" y1="4" x2="196" y2="196" stroke="#5a8c72" stroke-width="2"/>
                <polygon points="196,196 182,188 188,182" fill="#5a8c72"/>
                <line x1="4" y1="196" x2="196" y2="4" stroke="#5a8c72" stroke-width="2"/>
                <polygon points="196,4 182,12 188,18" fill="#5a8c72"/>
              </svg>
              <div class="ps-center"><div class="c-tag">Box A</div><div class="c-val">15% CP</div><div class="c-sub">required</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="ps-right">
              <div class="ps-res"><div class="r-tag">Box D — SBM parts</div><div class="r-eq">= |A − C| = |15 − 10|</div><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:700;color:#3d6b4f;margin-top:4px;">= 5 parts</div></div>
              <div class="ps-res ps-res-f"><div class="r-tag">Box F — Total parts</div><div class="r-eq">= D + E = 5 + 30</div><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:700;color:#7a5c00;margin-top:4px;">= 35 parts</div></div>
              <div class="ps-res"><div class="r-tag">Box E — Corn parts</div><div class="r-eq">= |B − A| = |45 − 15|</div><div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:700;color:#3d6b4f;margin-top:4px;">= 30 parts</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="w-step3" style="display:none;">
      <div class="worked-step">
        <h4>Step 3 — Convert parts to % of ration</h4>
        <p>Divide each ingredient's parts by the total parts (Box F), then multiply by 100.</p>
        <ol style="margin-top:10px;">
          <li><strong>Soybean meal</strong>: 5 parts ÷ 35 total parts = 0.143 × 100 = <strong>14.3% soybean meal</strong></li>
          <li style="margin-top:6px;"><strong>Corn</strong>: 30 parts ÷ 35 total parts = 0.857 × 100 = <strong>85.7% corn</strong></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="w-step4" style="display:none;">
      <div class="completion-banner show" style="margin-top:8px;">
        <div style="font-size:2.5rem;margin-bottom:10px">✅</div>
        <h2>Worked example complete!</h2>
        <p style="margin-top:10px;">Mix <strong>14.3% Soybean Meal</strong> with <strong>85.7% Corn</strong> to achieve a 15% CP ration.<br>
        Now try the interactive questions using the tabs above.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- /w-reveal-container -->

  <div style="margin-top:18px;">
    <button class="next-btn" id="w-reveal-btn" onclick="revealWorkedStep()">Show next step →</button>
  </div>

</div>
</div>

